<p>language codes for Html help</p>



<pre><code> 0x402 Bulgarian
 0x405 Czech
 0x406 Danish
 0x413 Dutch
 0xC09 English (Australia)
 0x809 English (Britain)
 0x1009 English (Canada)
 0x1809 English (Ireland)
 0x1409 English (New Zealand)
 0x1C09 English (South Africa)
 0x409 English (United States)
 0x40B Finnish
 0x40C French
 0x407 German
 0x408 Greece
 0x439 Hindi
 0x40E Hungarian
 0x410 Italian
 0x814 Norwegian
 0x415 Polish
 0x816 Portuguese(Portugal)
 0x416 Portuguese(Brazil)
 0x419 Russian
 0x80A Spanish(Mexico)
 0xC0A Spanish(Modern Sort)
 0x40A Spanish(Traditional Sort)
 0x41D Swedish
 0x41F Turkey
 0x411 Japanese
 0x412 Korean
 0x804 Chinese (PRC)
 0x404 Chinese (Taiwan)
</code></pre>


<p>New LCIDs:</p>



<pre><code> 0x421 Indonesian
 0x41A Croatian
 0x418 Romanian
 0x424 Slovenian
 0x41B Slovak
 0x422 Ukrainian
 0x81A Serbian (Serbia, Latin)
 0x403 Catalan
 0x426 Latvian
 0x427 Lithuanian
 0x436 Afrikaans
 0x42A Vietnamese
 0x429 Persian (Iran)
 0xC01 Arabic (Egypt) - I don't know which version of arabic is used inside <a href="/web-doxygen/docs/api/files/src/translator-ar-h">translator_ar.h</a> ,
       so I have chosen Egypt at random
</code></pre>


<p>Code for Esperanto should be as shown below but the htmlhelp compiler 1.3 does not support this (and no newer version is available).</p>



<pre><code>0x48f Esperanto
</code></pre>


<p>So do a fallback to the default language</p>



<pre><code>0x409 English (United States)
</code></pre>



<pre><code>0xC1A Serbian (Serbia, Cyrillic)
</code></pre>

<p>Used for identification of the language. May resemble the string returned by latexBabelPackage(), but it is not used for the same purpose. The identification should not be translated. It should be replaced by the name of the language in English (e.g. Czech, Japanese, Russian, etc.). It should be equal to the identification in <a href="/web-doxygen/docs/api/files/src/language-h">language.h</a>.</p>

Inside the text you can put the special marker $num to insert the number representing the actual number of search results. The <em>numDocuments</em> parameter can be either 0, 1 or 2, where the value 2 represents 2 or more matches. HTML markup is allowed inside the returned string.</p>
